He grew up in a Reform Jewish household, later describing it as "a standard non-Orthodox West Coast Jewish upbringingâ€”Hebrew school, bar mitzvah, and summer camp.
During his middle school years, he became rebellious and dabbled in drugs and petty crime until, at age 17, he attended a youth arts program and became interested in poetry.
In his early twenties, he visited North Dakota to participate in a Native American Sun Dance, during which he had a spiritual epiphany that inspired him to re-examine his Jewish roots.
That same year, he released his debut album, Waywordwonderwill, through Shemspeed Records.
After releasing two music videos, "The Screen Age" on September 21 and "Make America Hate Again" on October 12, the group released a self-titled EP on October 23, 2020.
